Police Parade Armed Robbery Suspects, Recover Arm It was a black Friday yesterday, as four vehicles collided on the Ojota-Maryland link bridge, at Odo Ita lya Alaro, Lagos. The incident led to the death of two persons, a male and a female.
 
The incident occurred when a commercial bus with six passengers on board coming from Mile 12 collided with a gasoline tanker with registration number FKJ-506XM and a Toyota Camry. 
  
Lagos State Environmental Health Monitoring Unit (SEHMU) took one of the bodies to the morgue while the other body simply identified as Blessing has her family members on the ground to take the body away.  “Several others persons were also injured and taken to nearby hospitals in Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) ambulance. LASAMBUS, LASEMA, NEMA, LASTMA, FRSC, LASAMBUS and Nigeria Police participated in the response,” he said.
 
Meanwhile, Lagos State Police Command has paraded suspected armed robbers and recovered arms and ammunition.  They recovered a silver-coloured Sienna bus with registration number LSR 509 HB, a locally made double barrel pistol, one machete, one knife, two screwdrivers, twelve mobile phones, one access bank ATM card with the name Newton Newman, some substances suspected to be Indian hemp and one dead snail and four live cartridges at Mojirade Street, Shibiri, Lagos.
  
According to the State’s Police Spokesman, the prompt arrest of the suspects followed a tip-off from Lagosians to the Divisional Police Officer of Ilemba Hausa Division who led his men to the criminal hideout where seven members of the gang were arrested while others fled.  